d form of English or Irish   Lacy  ."]},{"name":"Lacey","meanings":["English and Irish: variant of   Lacy  ."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice de Lacy was born in 1182, in Runcorn, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. She married Roger Pipard about 1190. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1237, in Dumfriesshire, Scotland, United Kingdom, at the age of 55."},"et":{"1182–1237":"1182–1237","1173–1245":"1173–1245","1164–Male":"1164–Surnud","1203–1245":"1203–1245","1212–1293":"1212–1293","1196–1227":"1196–1227","1227":"1227","1237":"1237","1203":"1203","1212":"1212","1245":"1245","1164":"1164","1196":"1196","about 1212":"umbes 1212","1173":"1173","ABT 1190":"umbes 1190","1293":"1293","1182":"1182","County Limerick, Ireland":"County Limerick, Iirimaa","Offaly,Kildare,Ireland":"Kildare, Edenderry, County Offaly, Iirimaa","Dunalamelin Castle, Ardee, Ireland":"Ardee, County Donegal, Iirimaa","Galloway, Dumfriesshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Dumfriesshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Runcorn, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Runcorn, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1182–1237":"1182–1237","1173–1245":"1173–1245","116